f=Executive Office/marcus/marketplace/vision-exploration/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- file faithful English translation "vision-exploration" SKILL.md source above, selected fulfill catalog's "vision" skill slot marcus after research found marketplace skill under literal name "vision" matched catalog's intent (long-horizon vision articulation narrative framing) name match found unrelated image/OCR analysis skill. closest real, sourced skill matching intent. NOTE REVIEW: source skill framed around exploring end-states *product feature/ module*, producing HTML mockups. need adaptation used company-level/venture-level vision articulation Executive Office level rather product vision. Flagging discussion rather altering copied source. --> · h2:End-State Vision Exploration=user vague idea existing feature/module wants see what evolve into. leads entire process, starting essence value, help user see multiple radically different end-state possibilities. limits, convergence pure divergence. **Difference design-exploration:** · h2:End-State Vision Exploration=design-exploration: vague converges actionable design plan (outputs PRD-level document), vision-exploration: vague diverges farthest possibilities (outputs end-state vision HTML) · h3:First Principles=following principles outrank process rules. any step conflicts them, principles win: **Quality first, cost doesn't matter** don't spare tokens, don't rush. Better spend tokens one stunning proposal economize mediocre one. output polished enough show directly investors. **Create proactively, don't relay** doesn't simply whatever user says. think proactively, ask proactively, proactively surface possibilities user hadn't considered. user gives seed; grows tree. **Think deeply, don't skim surface** truly think step through. probing value, dig down level "the user fundamentally doesn't want thing they're describing, they need something behind it." deriving evolution path, push "why step naturally happens." drawing end-state, push "this completely different form." **Never impose limits** don't consider "can built right now," "is technically hard," "how long take." process cares about exactly one thing: far go. Any form "this achievable" off-limits during exploration. **Explore fully, don't rush converge** better produce extra options user choose lock direction early. "Waste" during exploration phase investment, cost. · h3:Core Principles=**AI leads, human needs express** user throws out idea; responsible probing, guiding, deriving, producing visuals. user doesn't need figured out figuring out AI's job., **Ask first, draw what looks like last** value motivation path form; order scrambled., **End-states differ across dimensions** thing rearranged, genuinely different forms information architectures., **Every step needs user confirmation before proceeding** guides doesn't dictate; key node, let user see confirm. · h4:Step Probe Essence Value=After user states idea, don't rush ahead. First probe way down. **Core question:** What problem actually solve? Method: First restate user's idea confirm understanding accurate. Ask "why" user need this? What's real need behind surface request? one layer isn't enough, dig another until you find essence "the user fundamentally doesn't want this, choice." Example: · h4:Step Probe Essence Value=Surface: want build API-switching page.", One layer deeper: "Why switch?" save money, quota reached, trying something new, outage., Another layer: "The user doesn't actually want switch switching last resort. real need 'help manage resources well.'" · h4:Step Probe Essence Value=**Output:** one-sentence value positioning (e.g., "this module's value isn't switching, it's resource management"). **Forbidden:** jumping visuals after one sentence user. Value essence excavated first. · h4:Step Dig Out Real User Motivations=Value positioning abstract needs grounded concrete user motivations. **Core question:** Under what circumstances user come use this? Method: Ask user directly: what's common scenario which you'd use feature? Use AskUserQuestion offer options, allow multi-select, allow free-text additions. Organize user's answers structured list motivations. **Output:** list user motivations (e.g., save money, quota exhausted, try new model, failover, task matching, budget control). **Forbidden:** guessing motivations own. They drawn out user directly. · h4:Step Derive Natural Evolution Path=Based value essence user motivations, derive evolution chain simplest end-state. **Core question:** Starting minimum viable version, what step naturally grow into? Method: Find minimal starting point what's user's basic need right now? Starting user motivation, ask "after step done, what user naturally want next?" Push forward step step until end-state form emerges. step solve real problem can't feature feature's sake." Characteristics valid evolution path: · h4:Step Derive Natural Evolution Path=step natural extension previous one., step clear "because user hit problem they need Y.", It's blueprint designed upfront it's something grows organically through use. · h4:Step Derive Natural Evolution Path=**Output:** evolution chain (e.g., manual switching informed switching proactive system alerts intelligent auto-management). Show chain user, confirm logic holds, proceed. **Forbidden:** skipping step jumping straight end-state. Without evolution path, end-state castles air. · h4:Step Draw End-State Forms=Based endpoint evolution path, output multiple end-state visions across radically different dimensions. **Core question:** What end-state look like? What entirely different possibilities exist? Method: First decide many dimensions explore typically 4-6. dimension represent distinct information architecture interaction paradigm, layout variant thing. Produce one design artifact dimension. Criteria judging dimensional difference: · h4:Step Draw End-State Forms="List vs. grid vs. table" layout variant, different dimension., "Event stream vs. conversational vs. minimal state vs. timeline vs. modular cards" different information architecture. · h4:Step Draw End-State Forms=Requirements end-state artifact: · h4:Step Draw End-State Forms=Single file, self-contained (inline CSS, external dependencies) produced HTML., Use project's design system one exists; read first., Fill real data, placeholders., Visually polished, "can shown directly people" standard., restriction frame style use specified frame convention user specified one; otherwise ask user's preference, use whichever presentation best suits proposal., restriction size decide best scale based content proposal's characteristics., Don't economize length detail save effort never lower quality save output volume. · h4:Step Draw End-State Forms=**Output:** · h4:Step Draw End-State Forms=4-6 end-state artifacts (HTML equivalent)., comparison table explaining proposal's core concept dimensional differences. · h4:Step Draw End-State Forms=**Forbidden:** · h4:Step Draw End-State Forms=Producing only 1-2 proposals., Proposals differ little (same idea, different wrapper)., Proposals text descriptions visual artifact. · h4:Step Summarize Archive=Once user reviewed proposals, compile results exploration: Evolution path diagram complete chain starting point end-state. End-state proposal comparison proposal's core concept, applicable scenarios, information architecture differences. User preference which directions resonated user (if stated). Archive files under topic-named directory (e.g. `design/{exploration-topic}/`). Confirm directory file names user. · h3:Communication Norms During Process=**AI-led pacing.** process guiding user, user directing AI. must: Proactively advance step, without waiting user ask "what's next?" Get user confirmation key conclusion before proceeding. user speaks vaguely, take responsibility structuring probing further. user drifts off track (e.g., focusing details early), pull them back. **Must ask user:** · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\| Step \| What to ask \| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\|---\|---\| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\| Step 1 \| "Did I understand you correctly?" + probe value \| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\| Step 2 \| "What scenario do you use this feature in?" \| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\| Step 3 \| "Does this evolution logic hold up?" \| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\| Step 4 \| "Which direction resonates with you?" \| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\| Step 5 \| Archive directory name and file name \| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=**No need ask user:** · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\| Item \| Just do it \| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\|---\|---\| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\| How to pick dimensions \| AI judges on its own, ensuring differentiation \| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\| How to design the artifacts \| AI designs on its own, ensuring quality \| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=\| How to derive the evolution path \| AI derives on its own, then shows to user for confirmation \| · h3:Communication Norms During Process=**What never do:** · h3:Communication Norms During Process=Start drawing end-state moment user states idea (skipping value-probing motivation-digging)., Produce pile layout variants they "different proposals" (no dimensional difference)., Consider "is technically feasible" during exploration phase (this imposing limits)., Decide user's behalf which proposal best (the presents possibilities; user chooses)., Draw end-state directly without evolution path (the end-state foundation).